^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Taking the club finesse at trick 1 had merit. Even if it loses Roberta can then pitch her 2D losers on the Ace-Jack of clubs. However, once it wins, she has a chance to make six, by setting up the long club suit. Therefore, at trick 2 she can ruff a club then play two rounds of spades ending in dummy with the SJ  and ruff another club. She can then pitch her two diamonds on the A of clubs (upon which the K will fall) and the CJ. The more important point is Lisa must realize she has a game forcing hand over 1S.|
