ht|t|at|So, a minor suit bid shows a bad hand, and a major suit bid shows a good hand point count wise. Therefore, in the hand we just played, I play  that 3@D shows a bad hand with a good suit, and 3@H shows a good hand and a bad suit. However, there is another variation that Leandro plays which simply reverses 3@D and 3@H. In his version 3@D (which is what he bid originally) shows a good hand and a bad suit  and 3@H shows a bad hand and a good suit. In this variation the minors show a bad suit, and the majors show a good suit in his version. I don't think it matters which you play, although I believe, at least in the US, the version i play is more popular. But obviously you need to check with your partner.|
